summary: peter being a nervous wreck in the soul realm and when bucky asks him whats wrong he goes 'i really went and told mr. stark i...
body:
peter being a nervous wreck in the soul realm and when bucky asks him whats wrong he goes ‘i really went and told mr. stark i was sorry, like an idiot. hes gonna hate himself until he saves us all. hes gonna drink so much. i threw away all his emergency whiskey bottles but hes gonna break his promise and buy new ones. this is Bad’

and buckys at a loss for words because he had his “we’re gonna be okay, they will figure this out” speech ready but the kid got him thinking about how steve is probably staring at his hands and thinking that he failed to save bucky for the 4th time as if he had any say in this.

bucky ends up just sitting down next to peter and goes “those damn idiots will get themselves killed without us” and peter is like “right?? God heckin damn it”

summary: Tony made it so that Peter’s suit was hackable by Ned. And specifically Ned. He knew that hacking isn’t Peter’s thing and he...
body:
Tony made it so that Peter’s suit was hackable by Ned. And specifically Ned. He knew that hacking isn’t Peter’s thing and he also knew that Peter would only tell Ned when he was ready for it, and if he was ready to tell Ned, he was ready for all the gunctions the suit had to offer.

what a dad

blog.name: the-potato-one
blog.title: Drifting into the arena of the unwell
blog.description: This is a terrible Doctor Who blog ran by a posadist-egoist edgelord chunni who could have sworn this was deactivated years ago after Series 8. I mainly blog about the EU side of Doctor Who, with a dash of Fate/, whatever video game is on my mind and left wing politics. Native, Pan and whatever. Edging my way into the Faction Paradox books after listening to all 12 audios.  Also despite how bitter I am, I do feel like Moffat and RTD are capable of good writing. It just feels too rare at times to me.
